{
  "name": "RPlog_Coreshan_and_Morganna",
  "title": "Coreshan and Morganna",
  "summary": "In the Blue Nebula cantina, the musician Paul Nighman interviews the diver Eryk for a vague underwater expedition while the scarred, blaster-toting Morganna trades venomous barbs with Paul, briefly losing herself to a violent inner darkness. After Paul and Eryk conclude their business and leave, the haunted ex-Imperial Coreshan approaches Morganna, recounting his own story of guilt over the innocents he was made to kill and his quiet devotion to her. Their tense exchange, watched over by the lieutenant Ross and the patron KuhnDog, escalates as Coreshan draws his blaster only to set it aside, and the two agree to settle their standoff in the KOS Gardens. There, amid security cameras and blasted shrubbery, Morganna trains her weapon on Coreshan, who tries to convince her he would never betray her secret Imperial affiliations and that he cares for her. When he names her a slave to the Empire, the words cut deep; Morganna fires a stun bolt that misses, then flees in frustrated tears, while Coreshan, weeping, calls after her that someone still cares.",
